# Pi-hole DNS bypass / encrypted DNS resolver blocklist
# Purpose: prevent clients from resolving known DoH/DoT/DoQ resolver hostnames and bypassing local Pi-hole + Unbound.
# Notes:
# - This blocks resolver domains, not raw resolver IPs.
# - Also block outbound TCP/UDP 53 except Pi-hole/Unbound, TCP 853, UDP 853, UDP 784, UDP 8853, and known resolver IPs at router/firewall.
# - Avoid blocking broad provider roots like cloudflare.com, google.com, comcast.net, etc.

# DNS blocks
